FAQs 
1. What are the language requirements for studying in Latvia?
Most universities in Latvia offer programs in English, especially at the postgraduate level. Proficiency in English is typically required, and you may need to submit TOEFL or IELTS scores. Some programs are taught in Latvian, in which case proficiency in Latvian is necessary.

2. Are there scholarships available for international students in Latvia?
Yes, many Latvian universities and government programs offer scholarships to international students based on academic merit, financial need, or other criteria. These scholarships can help cover tuition fees and living expenses.

3. How much does it cost to live in Latvia as a student?
The cost of living in Latvia is generally affordable. Monthly expenses, including accommodation, food, transportation, and entertainment, can vary but are relatively low compared to many Western countries. On average, students might spend between $400 to $700 per month.
